result.adr_address: 106號 Tung Choi St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 106號 Tung Choi St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: Dim Dim Sum Mong Kok

reviews.text: We had a great experience here and went back twice! This is a modern and clean place. While we did not have to wait for a table, we did notice a queue form as we were eating. Menus are provided in english and you check the box for exactly what you want. Food was delicious! Reasonably priced at $2-3 per dish.

Such an awesome and unique menu. I love that the black bean spare ribs has taro instead of pumpkin in it. The soup dumplings were nice and savoury. The chili wonton had a strange flavour I just can't put my finger on but everything else was delicious.

Been here several times as it has great food and tea. Fresh, hot and tasty dim sums attracting both international and local clients. Brought many friends here and they have also enjoyed it very much. However, the door girl today was very rude. We had 4 people in total and ordered 3 teas. I asked whether it was mandatory that each person orders a tea and she said no, but advised us that we were not allowed to share the tea.... say what??? Are we allowed to share our food and maybe share our thoughts for the day??? 😒😒😒
Hence 4 stars!! Game up your customer service or you’ll find yourself losing business by the day.

Very good place to eat Dim Sum... We just walked in, had a few minutes to wait. Just walk in and they will give you the menu to choose. Service was very nice, even when not speaking English trying to explain the different food to us. You have to try the Crispy Rice Flour Rolls with shrimp, sweet and soft on the outside, crunchy on the inside. Very very good were the BBQ Pork Buns. We ordered way too much, but did eat everything...

Very tasty and good & various choice of dim sum. Good value for money. We were served very quickly. Famous place so lot of people but we did not have to wait long to get a table. Recommend the scallop dim sum, yummy !

result.adr_address: 香港旺角通菜街106號
result.name: 點點心

reviews.text:
길게 늘어선 줄 끝에 서서 한참을 기다렸는데, 알고보니 대기줄이 아니었음. 도착하면 무조건 카운터에 가서 메뉴와 대기표를 받아들고 순번을 기다려야 함. 무지한 탓에 도착순서에 비해 순번이 밀렸음. 토요일 저녁. 30여분 대기.
매장이 청결하고, 응대가 신속하며 친절한 편. 특히 카운터에 있는 누나가 엄청난 카리스마를 뿜뿜하면서 츤데레미를 뽑냄. 인상은 센데;; 이거저거 물어봐도 귀찮은 기색 없이 대답 잘해줌. 
여행 첫끼인데다 시장이 반찬임을 감안하더라도 별 여섯개 주고 싶은 맛. 새우 딤섬류는 홍콩 어딜가나 대체로 진리이기에 두 종류 주문했고, 어찌하다보니 찹쌀롤도 두 종류를 주문함. 기본 찹쌀롤은 쫀득하면서 고수향이 슬쩍 돌아 넘나 맛있고, 기본 찹쌀롤에 계란튀김옷?을 입혀 만든 또 다른 롤이 별거 아닌데도 별미임.

We had a great experience here and went back twice! This is a modern and clean place. While we did not have to wait for a table, we did notice a queue form as we were eating. Menus are provided in english and you check the box for exactly what you want. Food was delicious! Reasonably priced at $2-3 per dish.
